val</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <!-- Q6 -->\n  <h3>Can NZ players claim casino bonuses?</h3>\n  <p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> Yes \u2014 welcome bonuses, free spins, reloads and cashback are all available.</p>\n  <p>\n    Kiwi players can claim welcome bonuses, no-deposit offers, free-spin packages, reload bonuses and VIP rewards.  \n    Some casinos may exclude specific payment methods (e.g., Skrill or Neteller) from certain offers, so always \n    check the bonus terms before depositing.\n  </p>\n\n  <!-- Q7 -->\n  <h3>What are the signs of an unsafe offshore casino?</h3>\n  <p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> Fake licences, slow cashouts and unrealistic bonus claims.</p>\n  <p>Be cautious of casinos that show any of these red flags:</p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>No verifiable licence or unclear regulatory information</li>\n    <li>Repeated payout delays or cancelled withdrawals</li>\n    <li>Strange mirror URLs or lots of redirects</li>\n    <li>Extreme bonus offers (e.g., \u201c500 free spins no deposit!\u201d)</li>\n    <li>Pressure to use unusual payment methods</li>\n    <li>Support refusing to discuss withdrawal rules clearly</li>\n  </ul>\n\n  <!-- Q8 -->\n  <h3>What games are most popular at NZ online casinos?</h3>\n  <p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> Pokies (slots), live dealer games, blackjack, roulette and crash games.</p>\n  <p>\n    Kiwi players overwhelmingly prefer pokies, followed by live casino games, blackjack, roulette, game shows \n    and high-volatility crash titles.  \n    Pokies usually contribute 100% toward wagering, making them the most bonus-friendly option.\n  </p>\n\n  <!-- Q9 -->\n  <h3>Do online casinos require ID verification for NZ players?</h3>\n  <p><strong>Quick answer:</strong> Yes \u2014 all reputable casinos must verify your identity.</p>\n  <p>\n    Before you withdraw, offshore casinos must complete KYC checks. NZ players are usually required to provide:\n  </p>\n  <ul>\n    <li>A government-issued photo ID</li>\n    <li>A recent proof of